                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d383">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">368.1121 Stephano, Christopher/2: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-11T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 11, 1935—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12. Your 34, March 10, 9 p.m. While desirous of having its representatives extend
                    their good offices with a view to assuring proper treatment and just trial, the
                    Department feels that it could not properly intervene with the Greek Government
                    in behalf of American citizens who have contravened Greek law in such a serious
                    matter as rebellion unless there was strong reason to believe that otherwise a
                    grave miscarriage of justice would result.</p>
                <p>Please keep Department informed by telegraph concerning developments in Stephano
                    case and any other cases of a similar nature.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
